  <summary date="2017-01-11T05:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Relief from New Source Performance Standards Act of 2017

This bill delays by three years the date by which manufacturers, owners, and operators of new residential wood heaters, including residential hydronic heaters (wood-fired boilers) and forced-air furnaces, must comply with emission standards promulgated under the Clean Air Act.</summary>
